fuse metal segments, using processes such as gas tungsten arc, gas metal arc, flux-cored arc, plasma arc, shielded metal arc, resistance welding, and submerged arc welding</p></li><li><p>Monitor the fitting, burning, and welding processes to avoid overheating of parts or warping, shrinking, distortion, or expansion of material</p></li><li><p>Examine work pieces for defects and measure work pieces with straightedges or templates to ensure conformance with specifications</p></li><li><p>Recognize, set up, and operate hand and power tools common to the welding trade, such as shielded metal arc and gas metal arc welding equipment</p></li><li><p>Lay out, position, align, and secure parts and assemblies prior to assembly, using straightedges, combination squares, calipers, and rulers</p><p>&nbsp;</p></li></ol><p><br></p><p><b>Specific Skill Requirements/Competencies:</b></p><p><br></p><ul><li><p>Mechanically inclined</p></li><li><p>Willing to learn from others</p></li><li><p>Observing, receiving, and otherwise obtaining information from all relevant sources</p></li><li><p>Able to achieve goals in a fast-paced atmosphere</p></li></ul><p><br></p><p><b>Supervisory Responsibility: </b>None</p><br>\r\n\r\n                <br><p></p>\r\n                <p>\r\n\r\n                </p><div class=\"button-group\">\r\n                <!-- We\'ll always have the link to apply enabled since most users will not be\r\nlogged in when viewing this. Validation if the user can apply or not\r\nwill be done at WorkerApplyToJob action s-->\r\n                <a href=\"#\" onclick=\"ConfirmApply(\'https://app.tradesfactor.com/Jobs/WorkerApplyToJobFromSite/28\');\" class=\"button button-group-item primary w-button\">Apply now</a>\r\n            </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </div>'),
(23, '/images/company-icons-1.png', 'General Labor', ' - per year', '<div class=\"job-description\">\r\n            <div class=\"devider\"></div>\r\n            <div class=\"jobs-content text-medium align-left\">\r\n                <div class=\"location\"><a href=\"https://www.tradesfactor.com/company-jobs?company=7\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"\">Truck Accessories Group</a></div>\r\n                <div class=\"location\"><strong>Elkhart</strong></div>\r\n                <h5><strong>Job Description</strong></h5>\r\n                <p></p><p>\r\n\r\n            </p><div><p><b>ESSENTIAL DUTIES AND RESPONSIBLITIES</b>&nbsp;â€“ Duties may include:</p><ol><li>&nbsp;Apply resins and waxes to mold surfaces to facilitate assembly and removal of laminated parts</li><li>Apply layers of resin to mold surfaces prior to placement of fiberglass mats, repeating layers until product has desired thicknesses and plastics have hardened</li><li>Work with templates/patterns to conform with dimension &nbsp;data and/or customer specifications</li><li>Check completed products for conformance to specifics</li><li>Inspect, clean and assembly as needed</li><li>Mix catalyst into resins, use rollers, brushes and other hand tools to smooth fiberglass</li><li>Pat or press layers of saturated mat or cloth into place on molds, using brushes or hands, smooth out wrinkles and air bubbles with hands or rollers</li><li>Release air bubbles and smooth seams using rollers</li><li>Repair or modify damaged or defective parts, check thicknesses, density and contours to ensure proper fit.</li><li>Spray chopped fiberglass, resin and catalyst onto prepared molds using pneumatic spray guns with chopper attachments.</li><li>Trim cured materials using saws with diamond impregnated cutoff wheels</li><li>Trim excess materials from molds, using hand sheers or trimming knives</li></ol><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><b>QUALIFICATIONS</b></p><p>To perform this job successfully, and individual must be able to perform each 